sheShdslMib.contactinfo: Gerd Barchmann COO BBA DSLAM RD SDE HW1 gerd.barchmann@nsn.com
sheShdslMib.description: This MIB module defines a collection of objects for managing HDSL2/SHDSL lines according RFC3276. An agent may reside at either end of the line, however the MIB is designed to require no management communication between the modems beyond that inherent in the low-level EOC line protocol as defined in ANSI T1E1.4/2000-006 (for HDSL2 lines), or in ITU G.991.2 (for SHDSL lines). Adapted to support RFC 4319.

SheHdsl2ShdslTransmissionModeType.name: SheHdsl2ShdslTransmissionModeType
SheHdsl2ShdslTransmissionModeType.description: Contains the regional setting of the HDSL2/SHDSL span, represented as a bit-map of possible settings. The various bit positions are: Bit Meaning Description 1 region 1 Indicates ITU-T G.991.2 Annex A/F. 2 region 2 Indicates ITU-T G.991.2 Annex B/G.

SheHdsl2ShdslUnitId.name: SheHdsl2ShdslUnitId
SheHdsl2ShdslUnitId.description: This is the unique identification for all units in a HDSL2/SHDSL Span. It is based on the EOC unit addressing scheme with reference to the xtuC.

SheHdsl2ShdslUnitSide.name: SheHdsl2ShdslUnitSide
SheHdsl2ShdslUnitSide.description: This is the referenced side of a HDSL2/SHDSL unit - Network or Customer side. The side facing the Network is the Network side, while the side facing the Customer is the Customer side.

SheHdsl2ShdslWirePair.name: SheHdsl2ShdslWirePair
SheHdsl2ShdslWirePair.description: This is the referenced pair of wires in an HDSL2/SHDSL segment. HDSL2 only supports a single pair (wirePair1 or two wire), SHDSL lines support an optional second pair (wirePair2 or four wire), and G.shdsl.bis support an optional third pair (wirePair3 or six wire) and an optional fourth pair (wirePair4 or eight wire).

SheHdsl2ShdslPerfTimeElapsed.name: SheHdsl2ShdslPerfTimeElapsed
SheHdsl2ShdslPerfTimeElapsed.description: The number of seconds that have elapsed since the beginning of the current measurement period. If, for some reason, such as an adjustment in the system's time-of-day clock or the addition of a leap second, the current interval exceeds the maximum value, the agent will return the maximum value. For 15 minute intervals, the range is limited to (0..899). For 24 hour intervals, the range is limited to (0..86399).

SheHdsl2ShdslPerfCurrDayCount.name: SheHdsl2ShdslPerfCurrDayCount
SheHdsl2ShdslPerfCurrDayCount.description: A gauge associated with interface performance measurements in a current 1-day (24 hour) measurement interval. The value of this gauge starts at zero at the beginning of an interval and is increased when associated events occur, until the end of the 1-day interval. At that time the value of the gauge is stored in the previous 1-day history interval, as defined in a companion object of type Hdsl2Shdsl1DayIntevalCount, and the current interval gauge is restarted at zero. In the case where the agent has no valid data available for this interval the corresponding object instance is not available and upon a retrieval request a corresponding error message shall be returned to indicate that this instance does not exist. Please note that zero is a valid value.

SheHdsl2ShdslActivationStateType.name: SheHdsl2ShdslActivationStateType
SheHdsl2ShdslActivationStateType.description: Activation or training state of the wire pair.

SheHdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalCount.name: SheHdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalCount
SheHdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalCount.description: A counter associated with interface performance measurements during the most previous 1-day (24 hour) measurement interval. The value of this gauge is equal to the value of the current day gauge, as defined in a companion object of type Hdsl2ShdslPerfCurrDayCount, at the end of its most recent interval. In the case where the agent has no valid data available for this interval the corresponding object instance is not available and upon a retrieval request a corresponding error message shall be returned to indicate that this instance does not exist.

SheHdsl2ShdslClockReferenceType.name: SheHdsl2ShdslClockReferenceType
SheHdsl2ShdslClockReferenceType.description: The various STU-C symbol clock references for the HDSL2/SHDSL span, represented as an enumeration.

SheHdsl2ShdslTCLayerType.name: SheHdsl2ShdslTCLayerType
SheHdsl2ShdslTCLayerType.description: This textual convention represents possible ATMPTM-TC types in G.bond/Eth ports. The following values are defined: tc6465 - 64/65-octet encapsulation, as defined in [802.3] Clause 61.3.3 tcHDLC - HDLC encapsulation, as defined in [G.998.2] Annex B ATM - ATM based xDSL bonding, as defined in [G.998.1]

SheHdsl2ShdslPerfIntervalThreshold.name: SheHdsl2ShdslPerfIntervalThreshold
SheHdsl2ShdslPerfIntervalThreshold.description: This convention defines a range of values that may be set in a fault threshold alarm control. As the number of seconds in a 15-minute interval numbers at most 900, objects of this type may have a range of 0...900, where the value of 0 disables the alarm.

sheShdslCapabilityLineTxCap.name: sheShdslCapabilityLineTxCap
sheShdslCapabilityLineTxCap.description: This bitmap specifies the transmission modes that the STU-C is capable of supporting. Right now, support for Annex A (q9921PotsNonOverlapped(2) and q9921PotsOverlapped(3)) is present. This value depends on the DSL PHY firmware present on Columbia MxU.

sheShdslLineStatusTable.name: sheShdslLineStatusTable
sheShdslLineStatusTable.description: This MO is proprietary extension of RFC 3276 MIB and contains the proprietary line status. The table will only be supported for interfaces of iftype sdsl (96)!

sheShdslLineStatusEntry.name: sheShdslLineStatusEntry
sheShdslLineStatusEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dsShdslLineStatusTable. The Table is indexed by ifIndex. The table will only be supported for interfaces of iftype sdsl (96)!

sheShdslOpState.name: sheShdslOpState
sheShdslOpState.description: This object identifies the high level operational state for the STU.

sheShdslStartProgress.name: sheShdslStartProgress
sheShdslStartProgress.description: This object identifies the current detailed operational state of the STU.

sheShdslLineSwap.name: sheShdslLineSwap
sheShdslLineSwap.description: This object indicates if the physical lines are swapped, i.e., logical channel A is connected to physical channel B. This applies to 4-wire operation only.

sheShdslRmtCountryCode.name: sheShdslRmtCountryCode
sheShdslRmtCountryCode.description: This object provides the country code word, as defined in ITU-T G.991.2, for the STU at the other end of the loop. GlobespanVirata sets this to USA.

sheShdslRmtEncoderA.name: sheShdslRmtEncoderA
sheShdslRmtEncoderA.description: This object identifies the 21-bit value corresponding to encoder coefficient A, as defined in ITU-T G.991.2, for the STU at the other end of the loop.

sheShdslRmtEncoderB.name: sheShdslRmtEncoderB
sheShdslRmtEncoderB.description: This object identifies the 21-bit value corresponding to encoder coefficient B, as defined in ITU-T G.991.2, for the STU at the other end of the loop.

sheShdslRmtProviderCode.name: sheShdslRmtProviderCode
sheShdslRmtProviderCode.description: This object identifies the provider code word, as defined in ITU-T G.991.2, for the STU at the other end of the loop.

sheShdslLocDetect.name: sheShdslLocDetect
sheShdslLocDetect.description: This object is used to determine if carrier has been lost.

sheShdslTxPower.name: sheShdslTxPower
sheShdslTxPower.description: This object identifies the local STU transmit power in tenths of a dBm.

sheShdslFramerSync.name: sheShdslFramerSync
sheShdslFramerSync.description: This object returns information regarding the framer synchronization status.

sheShdslRmtTomData.name: sheShdslRmtTomData
sheShdslRmtTomData.description: This object provides vendor-provided data, as defined in ITU-T G.991.2, for the STU at the other end of the loop.

sheShdslDriftAlarm.name: sheShdslDriftAlarm
sheShdslDriftAlarm.description: This object identifies if the receive clock is in or out of range.

sheShdslReceiverGain.name: sheShdslReceiverGain
sheShdslReceiverGain.description: This object provides the total receiver gain in dB.

sheShdslBertError.name: sheShdslBertError
sheShdslBertError.description: This object provides the count of bit errors since the last time the object was read, as well as the type of synchronization.

sheShdslFramerOHAndDefects.name: sheShdslFramerOHAndDefects
sheShdslFramerOHAndDefects.description: This object returns overhead data. The four least significant bits contain the overhead data in the following format: bit 0 is losd, bit 1 is sega, bit 2 is ps, and bit 3 is segd.

sheShdslRmtFwVersion.name: sheShdslRmtFwVersion
sheShdslRmtFwVersion.description: This object provides the transceiver firmware release number of the STU at the other end of the loop.

sheShdslUtopiaCellDelineation.name: sheShdslUtopiaCellDelineation
sheShdslUtopiaCellDelineation.description: This object indicates whether cell delineation has been found.

sheShdslUtopiaRxCellCnt.name: sheShdslUtopiaRxCellCnt
sheShdslUtopiaRxCellCnt.description: This object indicates the number of UTOPIA cells received since the last time the object has been called. The maximum value is 0xFFFF.

sheShdslUtopiaCellDropCnt.name: sheShdslUtopiaCellDropCnt
sheShdslUtopiaCellDropCnt.description: This object indicates the number of UTOPIA cells dropped since the last time the object has been called. The maximum value is 0xFF.

sheShdslUtopiaRxHecErrorCnt.name: sheShdslUtopiaRxHecErrorCnt
sheShdslUtopiaRxHecErrorCnt.description: This object indicates the number of UTOPIA cells with HEC errors since the last time the object has been called. The maximum value is 0xFF.

sheShdslUtopiaTxCellCnt.name: sheShdslUtopiaTxCellCnt
sheShdslUtopiaTxCellCnt.description: This object indicates the number of UTOPIA cells transmitted since the last time the object has been called. The maximum value is 0xFFFF.

sheShdslRmtNsfCusId.name: sheShdslRmtNsfCusId
sheShdslRmtNsfCusId.description: This object returns the customer identification that was sent by the STU at the other end of the loop.

sheShdslRmtNsfCusData.name: sheShdslRmtNsfCusData
sheShdslRmtNsfCusData.description: This object returns non-standard format customer data that was sent by the STU at the other end of the loop.

sheShdslLocalHandshake.name: sheShdslLocalHandshake
sheShdslLocalHandshake.description: This object provides a way to see what capabilities are supported by the local STU. A total of 26 handshake parameters are supported.

sheShdslRemoteHandshake.name: sheShdslRemoteHandshake
sheShdslRemoteHandshake.description: This object provides a way to see what capabilities are supported by the STU at the other end of the loop. A total of 26 handshake parameters are supported.

sheShdslActualHandshake.name: sheShdslActualHandshake
sheShdslActualHandshake.description: This object provides the results of capabilities exchanged during handshake. A total of 26 handshake parameters are supported.

sheShdslRmtTxPower.name: sheShdslRmtTxPower
sheShdslRmtTxPower.description: This object provides the transmit power of the STU at the other end of the loop.

sheShdslRmtPowerBackoff.name: sheShdslRmtPowerBackoff
sheShdslRmtPowerBackoff.description: This object indicates whether power backoff is enabled or disabled at the STU at the other end of the loop.

sheShdslAutoRetrainCount.name: sheShdslAutoRetrainCount
sheShdslAutoRetrainCount.description: This object indicates the number of automatic retrains. This counter is only reset when a startup is initiated.

sheShdslEocState.name: sheShdslEocState
sheShdslEocState.description: This object provides status information about the eoc stage.

sheShdslFramerOneSecondCnt.name: sheShdslFramerOneSecondCnt
sheShdslFramerOneSecondCnt.description: This object provides CRC, SEGA, and LOSW defect one second error counts, and should be called every second.

sheShdslNtrFault.name: sheShdslNtrFault
sheShdslNtrFault.description: This object identifies the Network Timing Recovery Fault.

sheShdslParametricTestResult.name: sheShdslParametricTestResult
sheShdslParametricTestResult.description: Indicates the Result of the Parametric Test conducted on the Xcvr.

sheShdslParametricTestArray.name: sheShdslParametricTestArray
sheShdslParametricTestArray.description: Conexant parameter that indicates the Parametric Test Array.

sheShdslStartUpInfo.name: sheShdslStartUpInfo
sheShdslStartUpInfo.description: This conexant parameter indicates the startup mode, whether the lines comes up in bis mode or legacy mode (non bis).

sheShdslBisModeLocalHandshake.name: sheShdslBisModeLocalHandshake
sheShdslBisModeLocalHandshake.description: This conexant parameter provides a way to see what rates are supported by the local STU in the form of tuples.

sheShdslBisModeRemoteHandshake.name: sheShdslBisModeRemoteHandshake
sheShdslBisModeRemoteHandshake.description: This conexant parameter provides a way to see what rates are supported by the STU at other end of the loop in the form of tuples.

sheShdslBisModeActualHandshake.name: sheShdslBisModeActualHandshake
sheShdslBisModeActualHandshake.description: This conexant parametetr provides the results of rates exchanged during handshake in the form of tuples.

sheShdslLineParamsTable.name: sheShdslLineParamsTable
sheShdslLineParamsTable.description: This MO is proprietary extension of RFC 3276 MIB and contains the proprietary line parameters. The table will only be supported for interfaces of iftype sdsl (96)!

sheShdslLineParamsEntry.name: sheShdslLineParamsEntry
sheShdslLineParamsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dsShdslLineParamsTable. The Table is indexed by ifIndex. The table will only be supported for interfaces of iftype sdsl (96)!

sheShdslAction.name: sheShdslAction
sheShdslAction.description: This object specifies actions that are used to control transceiver operation.

sheShdslMode.name: sheShdslMode
sheShdslMode.description: This object specifies the operational mode of the transceiver.

sheShdslPowerScale.name: sheShdslPowerScale
sheShdslPowerScale.description: This object is used to compensate for minor differences in transmit power between designs.

sheShdslEncodeCoeffA.name: sheShdslEncodeCoeffA
sheShdslEncodeCoeffA.description: This object determines the value of encoder coefficient A, as defined in ITU-T G.991.2.

sheShdslEncodeCoeffB.name: sheShdslEncodeCoeffB
sheShdslEncodeCoeffB.description: This object determines the value of encoder coefficient B, as defined in ITU-T G.991.2

sheShdslTxEOCBufferLen.name: sheShdslTxEOCBufferLen
sheShdslTxEOCBufferLen.description: This object determines the number of bytes of EOC data that is buffered by the DSP in the transmit direction.

sheShdslRxEOCBufferLen.name: sheShdslRxEOCBufferLen
sheShdslRxEOCBufferLen.description: This object determines the number of bytes of EOC data that is buffered by the DSP in the receive direction.

sheShdslNTR.name: sheShdslNTR
sheShdslNTR.description: This object defines how network-timing recovery is performed.

sheShdslRxUpstreamFrameSync.name: sheShdslRxUpstreamFrameSync
sheShdslRxUpstreamFrameSync.description: Customer-defined value. This object defines the upstream frame sync word.

sheShdslRxDownstreamFrameSync.name: sheShdslRxDownstreamFrameSync
sheShdslRxDownstreamFrameSync.description: This object defines the downstream frame sync word.

sheShdslRxUpstreamStuffBits.name: sheShdslRxUpstreamStuffBits
sheShdslRxUpstreamStuffBits.description: Customer-defined value. This object defines the upstream.

sheShdslRxDownstreamStuffBits.name: sheShdslRxDownstreamStuffBits
sheShdslRxDownstreamStuffBits.description: This object defines the downstream stuff bits.

sheShdslInitiate.name: sheShdslInitiate
sheShdslInitiate.description: This object defines which STU initiates a startup. The default is STU-R initiates and STU-C waits.

sheShdslFramerRxClockMode.name: sheShdslFramerRxClockMode
sheShdslFramerRxClockMode.description: This object determines the source of the receive clock.

sheShdslFramerRxPllMode.name: sheShdslFramerRxPllMode
sheShdslFramerRxPllMode.description: This object enables or disables the internal PLL.

sheShdslSerialAtmCiuBufferSize.name: sheShdslSerialAtmCiuBufferSize
sheShdslSerialAtmCiuBufferSize.description: This object enables the user to set the size of the framer buffer for serial ATM operation.

sheShdslTxFramerPulseDelay.name: sheShdslTxFramerPulseDelay
sheShdslTxFramerPulseDelay.description: This parameter is for Serial ATM applications only. It is recommended that the default value be used. For special customer configurations, a delay of up to 7 clock cycles can be specified for the transmit frame pulse.

sheShdslRxFramerPulseDelay.name: sheShdslRxFramerPulseDelay
sheShdslRxFramerPulseDelay.description: This parameter is for Serial ATM applications only. It is recommended that the default value be used. For special customer configurations, a delay of up to 7 clock cycles can be specified for the receive frame pulse.

sheShdslMultiFrameMode.name: sheShdslMultiFrameMode
sheShdslMultiFrameMode.description: This object specifies the multi frame operational mode of the transceiver.

sheShdslEnable4or6MbpsBitrate.name: sheShdslEnable4or6MbpsBitrate
sheShdslEnable4or6MbpsBitrate.description: This object specifies the operational state of the 4_6Mbps bit rate.

sheShdslTomDataWord1.name: sheShdslTomDataWord1
sheShdslTomDataWord1.description: This object identifies one of four words of proprietary vendor data, as described in the Vendor Data section of ITU-T G.994.1.bis.

sheShdslTomDataWord2.name: sheShdslTomDataWord2
sheShdslTomDataWord2.description: This object identifies one of four words of proprietary vendor data, as described in the Vendor Data section of ITU-T G.994.1.bis.

sheShdslTomDataWord3.name: sheShdslTomDataWord3
sheShdslTomDataWord3.description: This object identifies one of four words of proprietary vendor data, as described in the Vendor Data section of ITU-T G.994.1.bis.

sheShdslTomDataWord4.name: sheShdslTomDataWord4
sheShdslTomDataWord4.description: This object identifies one of four words of proprietary vendor data, as described in the Vendor Data section of ITU-T G.994.1.bis.

sheShdslSetReqSilenceMode.name: sheShdslSetReqSilenceMode
sheShdslSetReqSilenceMode.description: This object enables a silent mode for the STU at the opposite end of the loop for approximately one minute. During the silent period, the STU that requested the silent mode could perform whatever operations it wants and the STU at the opposite end will remain in handshake.

sheShdslSetIndividualRates1.name: sheShdslSetIndividualRates1
sheShdslSetIndividualRates1.description: This item enables the user to individually enable or disable base rates for N=1 through N=16. The default is all rates enabled.

sheShdslSetIndividualRates2.name: sheShdslSetIndividualRates2
sheShdslSetIndividualRates2.description: This item enables the user to individually enable or disable base rates for N=17 through N=32. The default is all rates enabled.

sheShdslSetIndividualRates3.name: sheShdslSetIndividualRates3
sheShdslSetIndividualRates3.description: This item enables the user to individually enable or disable base rates for N=33 through N=36. The default is all rates enabled.

sheShdslSatmCellDelineation.name: sheShdslSatmCellDelineation
sheShdslSatmCellDelineation.description: This object enables the user to enable or disable cell delineation for serial ATM operation. This parameter should be set before a startup.

sheShdslFramerCellDropOnError.name: sheShdslFramerCellDropOnError
sheShdslFramerCellDropOnError.description: This object determines whether cells are dropped, i.e., not passed to the host, or not dropped, i.e., passed to the host. This object must be set prior to startup.

sheShdslGearShiftType.name: sheShdslGearShiftType
sheShdslGearShiftType.description: This object specifies the Gear Shift Type.

sheShdslHsNsf.name: sheShdslHsNsf
sheShdslHsNsf.description: This object enables or disables nonstandard Information fields for MP, MS, CL, and CLR messages, as defined in ITU-T G.994.1.bis.

sheShdslHsMaxBitsPerBaud.name: sheShdslHsMaxBitsPerBaud
sheShdslHsMaxBitsPerBaud.description: This object specifies the maximum bit per baud.

sheShdslHsCusId.name: sheShdslHsCusId
sheShdslHsCusId.description: This object identifies the customer identification during handshaking, as described in ITU-T G.994.1.bis.

sheShdslHsCusData0.name: sheShdslHsCusData0
sheShdslHsCusData0.description: This object identifies two words of customer data during handshaking, as defined in ITU-T G.994.1.bis.

sheShdslHsCusData1.name: sheShdslHsCusData1
sheShdslHsCusData1.description: This object identifies two words of customer data during handshaking, as defined in ITU-T G.994.1.bis.

sheShdslHsAnnexBType.name: sheShdslHsAnnexBType
sheShdslHsAnnexBType.description: This object allows the customer to choose between support for Annex B, Annex B with Access Network Frequency Plan (ANFP), or both.

sheShdslArCrcCheck.name: sheShdslArCrcCheck
sheShdslArCrcCheck.description: Enables or disables auto-retrain based on CRC errors.

sheShdslArFramerSyncCheck.name: sheShdslArFramerSyncCheck
sheShdslArFramerSyncCheck.description: Enables or disables auto-retrain based on framer synchronization.

sheShdslArSnrMarginCheck.name: sheShdslArSnrMarginCheck
sheShdslArSnrMarginCheck.description: Enables or disables auto-retrain based on whether the S/N margin falls below a preset threshold.

sheShdslArCrcThreshold.name: sheShdslArCrcThreshold
sheShdslArCrcThreshold.description: Sets the threshold for the number of frames with CRC errors for autoretrain.

sheShdslArSnrMarginThreshold.name: sheShdslArSnrMarginThreshold
sheShdslArSnrMarginThreshold.description: Set the margin threshold for autoretrain.

sheShdslArRetrainTime.name: sheShdslArRetrainTime
sheShdslArRetrainTime.description: Sets the time over which the autoretrain parameters must be outside their normal ranges, so that an auto-retrain occurs.

sheShdslOpStateTrapEnable.name: sheShdslOpStateTrapEnable
sheShdslOpStateTrapEnable.description: Enables/disables trap indicating a change in op state.

sheShdslTxFrmrDataClkEdge.name: sheShdslTxFrmrDataClkEdge
sheShdslTxFrmrDataClkEdge.description: This parameter is for Serial ATM applications only. It is recommended that the default value be used. For special customer configurations, transmit data can be sampled upon either rising or falling edge of the transmit clock.

sheShdslRxFrmrDataClkEdge.name: sheShdslRxFrmrDataClkEdge
sheShdslRxFrmrDataClkEdge.description: This parameter is for Serial ATM applications only. It is recommended that the default value be used. For special customer configurations, receive data can be valid upon either rising or falling edge of the receive clock.

sheShdslTxFrmrPulseClkEdge.name: sheShdslTxFrmrPulseClkEdge
sheShdslTxFrmrPulseClkEdge.description: This parameter is for Serial ATM applications only. It is recommended that the default value be used. For special customer configurations, the transmit frame pulse can be active upon either rising or falling edge.

sheShdslRxFrmrPulseClkEdge.name: sheShdslRxFrmrPulseClkEdge
sheShdslRxFrmrPulseClkEdge.description: This parameter is for Serial ATM applications only. It is recommended that the default value be used. For special customer configurations, the transmit frame pulse can be active upon either rising or falling edge.

sheShdslTxFrmrPulseLvl.name: sheShdslTxFrmrPulseLvl
sheShdslTxFrmrPulseLvl.description: This parameter is for Serial ATM applications only. It is recommended that the default value be used. For special customer configurations, the transmit frame pulse can be either active high (1) or active low (0).

sheShdslRxFrmrPulseLvl.name: sheShdslRxFrmrPulseLvl
sheShdslRxFrmrPulseLvl.description: This parameter is for Serial ATM applications only. It is recommended that the default value be used. For special customer configurations, the transmit frame pulse can be either active high (1) or active low (0).

sheShdslFrmrOH.name: sheShdslFrmrOH
sheShdslFrmrOH.description: This object specifies framer OverHead Channel.

sheShdslLoopAttenCrossingTrapEnable.name: sheShdslLoopAttenCrossingTrapEnable
sheShdslLoopAttenCrossingTrapEnable.description: This Parameter enables or disables the Trap for Loop Attenuation Threshold crossing.

sheShdslSNRMarginCrossingTrapEnable.name: sheShdslSNRMarginCrossingTrapEnable
sheShdslSNRMarginCrossingTrapEnable.description: This Parameter enables or disables the Trap for SNR Margin Threshold crossing.

sheShdslFramerOHAndDefectsTrapEnable.name: sheShdslFramerOHAndDefectsTrapEnable
sheShdslFramerOHAndDefectsTrapEnable.description: This Parameter enables or disables the Trap for Framer Overhead and Defects.

sheShdslParametricTestInputFile.name: sheShdslParametricTestInputFile
sheShdslParametricTestInputFile.description: Indicates Name of the Input file from which to take the Mask Array Size, lower and upper mask Array. Null string means no file is specified.

sheShdslParamHybridLossTestStart.name: sheShdslParamHybridLossTestStart
sheShdslParamHybridLossTestStart.description: Indicates Start bin for range of bins to be measured. The default value mentioned is an indicative value only, for exact value refer to document number DO-400523-AN and DO-401163-AN.

sheShdslParamHybridLossTestEnd.name: sheShdslParamHybridLossTestEnd
sheShdslParamHybridLossTestEnd.description: Indicates End bin for range of bins to be measured. The default value mentioned is an indicative value only.

sheShdslFramerType.name: sheShdslFramerType
sheShdslFramerType.description: This object defines which type of data interface type is used. Note that the non-default values only apply to Conexant chips that support serial interfaces.

sheShdslAFEType.name: sheShdslAFEType
sheShdslAFEType.description: This objects defines which AFE is being used.

sheShdslUtopiaL2TxAddress.name: sheShdslUtopiaL2TxAddress
sheShdslUtopiaL2TxAddress.description: This object selects the appropriate UTOPIA Level 2 address for the transmit interface.

sheShdslUtopiaL2RxAddress.name: sheShdslUtopiaL2RxAddress
sheShdslUtopiaL2RxAddress.description: This object selects the appropriate UTOPIA Level 2 address for the receive interface.

sheShdslUtopiaDataBusWidth.name: sheShdslUtopiaDataBusWidth
sheShdslUtopiaDataBusWidth.description: This parameter is used to specify width of UTOPIA data bus.

sheShdslPAMMode.name: sheShdslPAMMode
sheShdslPAMMode.description: This parameter is used to configure the PAM mode value for startup.

sheShdslLineParamsControlRequest.name: sheShdslLineParamsControlRequest
sheShdslLineParamsControlRequest.description: modifyShdslLineParamsEntry a complete set of configurable parameters according the sheShdlsLinParamsControl-group.

sheShdslLineParamsControlStatus.name: sheShdslLineParamsControlStatus
sheShdslLineParamsControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

sheShdslLineParamsControlTimer.name: sheShdslLineParamsControlTimer
sheShdslLineParamsControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

sheShdslLineParamsControlReqResult.name: sheShdslLineParamsControlReqResult
sheShdslLineParamsControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

sheShdslLineParamsControlTimeStamp.name: sheShdslLineParamsControlTimeStamp
sheShdslLineParamsControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheShdslSpanStatusExtnTable.name: sheShdslSpanStatusExtnTable
sheShdslSpanStatusExtnTable.description: This table is a proprietary extension of hdsl2ShdslSpanStatusTable. The table will only be supported for interfaces of iftype sdsl (96)!

sheShdslSpanStatusExtnEntry.name: sheShdslSpanStatusExtnEntry
sheShdslSpanStatusExtnEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dsShdslSpanStatusExtnTable. The Table is indexed by ifIndex. The table will only be supported for interfaces of iftype sdsl (96)!

sheShdslStatusPMMSMaxLineRate.name: sheShdslStatusPMMSMaxLineRate
sheShdslStatusPMMSMaxLineRate.description: This object provides the maximum PMMS rate the line is capable of achieving

sheShdslStatus4WireHsMode.name: sheShdslStatus4WireHsMode
sheShdslStatus4WireHsMode.description: Contains the current 4 Wire Handshake Mode Configured

sheShdslBondingGroupTable.name: sheShdslBondingGroupTable
sheShdslBondingGroupTable.description: This table contains a fixed set of possible bondig group entrys. This table will not longer be supported.

sheShdslBondingGroupEntry.name: sheShdslBondingGroupEntry
sheShdslBondingGroupEntry.description: This table contains a fixed set of possible bondig group entrys. Index is the ifIndex from if-table (used iftype is 143 - msdsl - multirate sdsl). Entry will be created and deleted during card create or delete for a shdsl-card. For one shdsl card with 48 shdsl lines, this table will contain 24 groups of type twoPortsBondingGroup and 12 entrys of type fourPortsBondingGroup.

sheShdslBondingGroupBridgePortList.name: sheShdslBondingGroupBridgePortList
sheShdslBondingGroupBridgePortList.description: Portlist for all member of this bonding group. The octet string is a list of pairs of octets each identify an sheBridgePortIndex. The least significant byte is the second octet.

sheShdslBondingGroupType.name: sheShdslBondingGroupType
sheShdslBondingGroupType.description: The type descripes if this group contain 2 or 4 shdsl - lines.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfTable.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfTable
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfTable.description: This table supports overall configuration of HDSL2/SHDSL Spans. Entries in this table MUST be maintained in a persistent manner.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfEntry.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfEntry
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfEntry.description: An entry in the hdsl2ShdslSpanConfTable. Each entry represents the complete Span in a single SHDSL line. It is indexed by the ifIndex of the associated HDSL2/SHDSL line.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfNumRepeaters.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfNumRepeaters
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfNumRepeaters.description: This object provisions the number of repeaters/regenerators in this HDSL2/SHDSL Span. The System will not support repeaters.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfile.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfile
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfile.description: This object is a pointer to a span configuration profile in the hdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileTable, which applies to this span. The value of this object is the index of the referenced profile in the hdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileTable. Any attempt to set this object to a value that is not the value of the index for an active entry in the profile table, hdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileTable, MUST be rejected.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfAlarmProfile.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfAlarmProfile
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfAlarmProfile.description: This object is a pointer to an Alarm configuration profile in the hdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileTable. The value of this object is the index of the referenced profile in the hdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileTable. The alarm threshold configuration in the referenced profile will be used by default for all segment endpoints in this span. Individual endpoints may override this profile by explicitly specifying some other profile in the hdsl2ShdslEndpointConfTable. By default, this object will have the value 'DEFVAL' (the index of the default profile). Any attempt to set this object to a value that is not the value of the index for an active entry in the profile table, hdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileTable, MUST be rejected.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfControlStatus.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfControlStatus
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfControlTimer.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfControlTimer
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfControlReqResult.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfControlReqResult
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfControlTimeStamp.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfControlTimeStamp
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

shehdsl2ShdslSpanStatusTable.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanStatusTable
shehdsl2ShdslSpanStatusTable.description: This table provides overall status information of HDSL2/SHDSL spans. This table contains live data from equipment. As such, it is NOT persistent.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanStatusEntry.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanStatusEntry
shehdsl2ShdslSpanStatusEntry.description: An entry in the hdsl2ShdslSpanStatusTable. Each entry represents the complete span in a single HDSL2/SHDSL line. It is indexed by the ifIndex of the associated HDSL2/SHDSL line.

shehdsl2ShdslStatusNumAvailRepeaters.name: shehdsl2ShdslStatusNumAvailRepeaters
shehdsl2ShdslStatusNumAvailRepeaters.description: Contains the actual number of repeaters/regenerators discovered in this HDSL2/SHDSL span.

shehdsl2ShdslStatusMaxAttainableLineRate.name: shehdsl2ShdslStatusMaxAttainableLineRate
shehdsl2ShdslStatusMaxAttainableLineRate.description: Contains the maximum attainable line rate in this HDSL2/SHDSL span. This object provides the maximum rate the line is capable of achieving. This is based upon measurements made during line probing. This rate includes payload (user data) and any applicable framing overhead.

shehdsl2ShdslStatusActualLineRate.name: shehdsl2ShdslStatusActualLineRate
shehdsl2ShdslStatusActualLineRate.description: Contains the actual line rate in this HDSL2/SHDSL span. This should equal ifSpeed. This rate includes payload (user data) and any applicable framing overhead.

shehdsl2ShdslStatusTransmissionModeCurre.name: shehdsl2ShdslStatusTransmissionModeCurrent
shehdsl2ShdslStatusTransmissionModeCurre.description: Contains the current Power Spectral Density (PSD) regional setting of the HDSL2/SHDSL span. Bit Meaning Description 1 region 1 Indicates ITU-T G.991.2 Annex A/F. 2 region 2 Indicates ITU-T G.991.2 Annex B/G.

sheShdslStatusMaxAttainablePayloadRate.name: sheShdslStatusMaxAttainablePayloadRate
sheShdslStatusMaxAttainablePayloadRate.description: This parameter contains the maximum attainable payload rate in this SHDSL span. This is based upon measurements made during line probing without including any framing overhead.

sheShdslStatusActualPayloadRate.name: sheShdslStatusActualPayloadRate
sheShdslStatusActualPayloadRate.description: This parameter contains the actual payload rate in this SHDSL span. This is based upon measurements made during line probing without including any framing overhead.

sheShdslSpanStatusPAMModulation.name: sheShdslSpanStatusPAMModulation
sheShdslSpanStatusPAMModulation.description: The parameter show the selected PAM constellation is to be used. - SELECT_16_PAM - Use 16 PAM only - SELECT_32_PAM - Use 32 PAM only Select 16Pam limits the data rates from 192 kbps to 3840 kbps Select 32Pam limits the data rates from 768 kbps to 5696 kbps This is propietary extension for interfaces of type shdsl (169) only.

shehdsl2ShdslInventoryTable.name: shehdsl2ShdslInventoryTable
shehdsl2ShdslInventoryTable.description: This table supports retrieval of unit inventory information available via the EOC from units in a HDSL2/SHDSL line. Entries in this table are dynamically created during the line discovery process. The life cycle for these entries is as follows: - xtu discovers a device, either a far-end xtu or an xru - an inventory table entry is created for the device - the line goes down for whatever reason - inventory table entries for unreachable devices are destroyed. As these entries are created/destroyed dynamically, they are NOT persistent.

shehdsl2ShdslInventoryEntry.name: shehdsl2ShdslInventoryEntry
shehdsl2ShdslInventoryEntry.description: An entry in the hdsl2ShdslInventoryTable. Each entry represents inventory information for a single unit in a HDSL2/SHDSL line. It is indexed by the ifIndex of the HDSL2/SHDSL line and the Hdsl2ShdslUnitId of the associated unit.

shehdsl2ShdslInvIndex.name: shehdsl2ShdslInvIndex
shehdsl2ShdslInvIndex.description: Each entry in this table corresponds to a physical element in a HDSL2/SHDSL Span. It is based on the EOC unit addressing scheme with reference to the xtuC.

shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorID.name: shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorID
shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorID.reference: G.991.2, Section 9.5.5.7.4, Inventory response - Message ID 130, Octets 25-32.
shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorID.description: Vendor ID as reported in an Inventory Response message.

shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorModelNumber.name: shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorModelNumber
shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorModelNumber.reference: G.991.2, Section 9.5.5.7.4, Inventory response - Message ID 130, Octets 33-44.
shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorModelNumber.description: Vendor model number as reported in an Inventory Response message.

shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorSerialNumber.name: shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorSerialNumber
shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorSerialNumber.reference: G.991.2, Section 9.5.5.7.4, Inventory response - Message ID 130, Octets 45-56.
shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorSerialNumber.description: Vendor serial number as reported in an Inventory Response message.

shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorEOCSoftwareVersion.name: shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorEOCSoftwareVersion
shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorEOCSoftwareVersion.reference: G.991.2, Section 9.5.5.7.2, Discovery response - Message ID 129, Octet 12
shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorEOCSoftwareVersion.description: Vendor EOC version as reported in a Discovery Response message.

shehdsl2ShdslInvStandardVersion.name: shehdsl2ShdslInvStandardVersion
shehdsl2ShdslInvStandardVersion.reference: G.991.2, Section 9.5.5.7.4, Inventory response - Message ID 130, Octet 2
shehdsl2ShdslInvStandardVersion.description: Version of the HDSL2/SHDSL standard implemented, as reported in an Inventory Response message.

shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorListNumber.name: shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorListNumber
shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorListNumber.reference: G.991.2, Section 9.5.5.7.4, Inventory response - Message ID 130, Octets 3-5
shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorListNumber.description: Vendor list number as reported in an Inventory Response message.

shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorIssueNumber.name: shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorIssueNumber
shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorIssueNumber.reference: G.991.2, Section 9.5.5.7.4, Inventory response - Message ID 130, Octets 6-7.
shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorIssueNumber.description: Vendor issue number as reported in an Inventory Response message.

shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorSoftwareVersion.name: shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorSoftwareVersion
shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorSoftwareVersion.reference: G.991.2, Section 9.5.5.7.4, Inventory response - Message ID 130, Octets 8-13.
shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorSoftwareVersion.description: Vendor software version as reported in an Inventory Response message.

shehdsl2ShdslInvEquipmentCode.name: shehdsl2ShdslInvEquipmentCode
shehdsl2ShdslInvEquipmentCode.reference: G.991.2, Section 9.5.5.7.4, Inventory response - Message ID 130, Octets 14-23.
shehdsl2ShdslInvEquipmentCode.description: Equipment code conforming to ANSI T1.213, Coded Identification of Equipment Entities.

shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorOther.name: shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorOther
shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorOther.reference: G.991.2, Section 9.5.5.7.4, Inventory response - Message ID 130, Octets 57-68.
shehdsl2ShdslInvVendorOther.description: Other vendor information as reported in an Inventory Response message.

shehdsl2ShdslInvTransmissionModeCapabili.name: shehdsl2ShdslInvTransmissionModeCapability
shehdsl2ShdslInvTransmissionModeCapabili.description: Contains the transmission mode capability of the SHDSL unit. Bit Meaning Description 1 region 1 Indicates ITU-T G.991.2 Annex A/F. 2 region 2 Indicates ITU-T G.991.2 Annex B/G.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfTable.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfTable
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfTable.description: This table supports configuration parameters for segment endpoints in a HDSL2/SHDSL line. As this table is indexed by ifIndex, it MUST be maintained in a persistent manner.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfEntry.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfEntry
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfEntry.description: An entry in the hdsl2ShdslEndpointConfTable. Each entry represents a single segment endpoint in a HDSL2/SHDSL line. It is indexed by the ifIndex of the HDSL2/SHDSL line, the UnitId of the associated unit, the side of the unit, and the wire-pair of the associated modem.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointSide.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointSide
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointSide.description: The side of the unit associated with this segment endpoint - Network/Customer side - as per the Hdsl2ShdslUnitSide textual convention.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointWirePair.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointWirePair
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointWirePair.description: The wire-pair of the modem associated with this segment endpoint as per the Hdsl2ShdslWirePair textual convention. wirePair1(1), -> two wire wirePair2(2), -> four wire wirePair3(3), -> six wire wirePair4(4) -> eight wire

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfile.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfile
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfile.description: This object configures the alarm threshold values to be used for this segment endpoint. The values are obtained from the alarm configuration profile referenced by this object. The value of this object is the index of the referenced profile in the hdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileTable, or NULL (a zero- length SnmpAdminString). If the value is a zero-length SnmpAdminString, the endpoint uses the default Alarm Configuration Profile for the associated span as per the hdsl2ShdslSpanConfAlarmProfile object in the hdsl2ShdslSpanConfTable. The default value of this object is a zero-length SnmpAdminString. Any attempt to set this object to a value that is not the value of the index for an active entry in the profile table, hdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileTable, MUST be rejected.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfControlIndex.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfControlIndex
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfControlIndex.description: First key for the modified entry. IfIndex of line.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfControlStatus.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfControlStatus
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfControlTimer.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfControlTimer
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfControlReqResul.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfControlReqResult
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfControlReqResul.description: The result of the last user command.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfControlTimeStam.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfControlTimeStamp
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfControlTimeStam.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfControlSide.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfControlSide
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfControlSide.description: Third key for the modified entry.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfControlWirePair.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfControlWirePair
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointConfControlWirePair.description: Forth key for the modified entry.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrTable.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrTable
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrTable.description: This table contains current status and performance information for segment endpoints in HDSL2/SHDSL Lines. As with other tables in this MIB indexed by ifIndex, entries in this table MUST be maintained in a persistent manner.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrEntry.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrEntry
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrEntry.description: An entry in the hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrTable. Each entry contains status and performance information relating to a single segment endpoint. It is indexed by the ifIndex of the HDSL2/SHDSL line, the UnitId of the associated unit, the side of the unit, and the wire-pair of the associated modem.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrAtn.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrAtn
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrAtn.description: The current loop attenuation for this endpoint as reported in a Network or Customer Side Performance Status message.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrSnrMgn.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrSnrMgn
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrSnrMgn.description: The current SNR margin for this endpoint as reported in a Status Response/SNR message.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrStatus.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrStatus
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrStatus.description: Contains the current state of the endpoint. This is a bitmap of possible conditions. The various bit positions are: noDefect There no defects on the line. powerBackoff Indicates enhanced Power Backoff. deviceFault Indicates a vendor-dependent diagnostic or self-test fault has been detected. dcContinuityFault Indicates vendor-dependent conditions that interfere with span powering such as short and open circuits. snrMarginAlarm Indicates that the SNR margin has dropped below the alarm threshold. loopAttenuationAlarm Indicates that the loop attenuation exceeds the alarm threshold. loswFailureAlarm Indicates a forward LOSW alarm. configInitFailure Endpoint failure during initialization due to paired endpoint not able to support requested configuration. protocolInitFailure Endpoint failure during initialization due to incompatible protocol used by the paired endpoint. noNeighborPresent Endpoint failure during initialization due to no activation sequence detected from paired endpoint. loopbackActive A loopback is currently active at this Segment Endpoint. This is intended to supplement ifOperStatus. Note that there is a 1-1 relationship between the status bits defined in this object and the notification thresholds defined elsewhere in this MIB.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointES.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointES
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointES.description: Count of Errored Seconds (ES) on this endpoint since the xU was last restarted.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointSES.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointSES
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointSES.description: Count of Severely Errored Seconds (SES) on this endpoint since the xU was last restarted.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCRCanomalies.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCRCanomalies
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCRCanomalies.description: Count of CRC anomalies on this endpoint since the xU was last restarted.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointLOSWS.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointLOSWS
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointLOSWS.description: Count of Loss of Sync Word (LOSW) Seconds on this endpoint since the xU was last restarted.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointUAS.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointUAS
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointUAS.description: Count of Unavailable Seconds (UAS) on this endpoint since the xU was last restarted.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinTimeElapse.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinTimeElapsed
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinTimeElapse.description: Total elapsed seconds in the current 15-minute interval.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinES.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinES
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinES.description: Count of Errored Seconds (ES) in the current 15-minute interval.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinSES.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinSES
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinSES.description: Count of Severely Errored Seconds (SES) in the current 15-minute interval.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinCRCanomali.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinCRCanomalies
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinCRCanomali.description: Count of CRC anomalies in the current 15-minute interval.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinLOSWS.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinLOSWS
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinLOSWS.description: Count of Loss of Sync Word (LOSW) Seconds in the current 15-minute interval.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinUAS.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinUAS
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr15MinUAS.description: Count of Unavailable Seconds (UAS) in the current 15-minute interval.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayTimeElapsed.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayTimeElapsed
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayTimeElapsed.description: Number of seconds that have elapsed since the beginning of the current 1-day interval.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayES.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayES
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayES.description: Count of Errored Seconds (ES) during the current day as measured by hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DaySES.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DaySES
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DaySES.description: Count of Severely Errored Seconds (SES) during the current day as measured by hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayCRCanomalie.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayCRCanomalies
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayCRCanomalie.description: Count of CRC anomalies during the current day as measured by hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayLOSWS.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayLOSWS
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayLOSWS.description: Count of Loss of Sync Word (LOSW) Seconds during the current day as measured by hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayUAS.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayUAS
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayUAS.description: Count of Unavailable Seconds (UAS) during the current day as measured by hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrTipRingReversal.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrTipRingReversal
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrTipRingReversal.description: This object indicates the state of the tip/ring for the wire pair. normal(1), reversed(2)

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrActivationState.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrActivationState
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrActivationState.reference: ITU-T G.991.2, Section 6.2 PMD Activation Sequence
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrActivationState.description: This object indicates the activation or training state of the wire pair. preActivation(1), -> PreTrain activation(2), -> Training data(3) -> Trained

shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalTable.name: shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalTable
shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalTable.description: This table provides one row for each HDSL2/SHDSL endpoint performance data collection interval. This table contains live data from equipment. As such, it is NOT persistent.

shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalNumber.name: shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalNumber
shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalNumber.description: Performance Data Interval number. 1 is the the most recent previous interval; interval 96 is 24 hours ago. Intervals 2..96 are optional.

shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalEndTime.name: shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalEndTime
shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalEndTime.description: This variable indicates the time of storing this interval.

shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalES.name: shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalES
shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalES.description: Count of Errored Seconds (ES) during the interval.

shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalSES.name: shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalSES
shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalSES.description: Count of Severely Errored Seconds (SES) during the interval.

shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalCRCanomalies.name: shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalCRCanomalies
shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalCRCanomalies.description: Count of CRC anomalies during the interval.

shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalLOSWS.name: shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalLOSWS
shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalLOSWS.description: Count of Loss of Sync Word (LOSW) Seconds during the interval.

shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalUAS.name: shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalUAS
shehdsl2Shdsl15MinIntervalUAS.description: Count of Unavailable Seconds (UAS) during the interval.

shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalTable.name: shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalTable
shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalTable.description: This table provides one row for each HDSL2/SHDSL endpoint performance data collection interval. This table contains live data from equipment. As such, it is NOT persistent.

shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalNumber.name: shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalNumber
shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalNumber.description: History Data Interval number. Interval 1 is the the most recent previous day; interval 30 is 30 days ago. Intervals 2..30 are optional.

shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalEndTime.name: shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalEndTime
shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalEndTime.description: This variable indicates the time of storing this interval.

shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalMoniSecs.name: shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalMoniSecs
shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalMoniSecs.description: The amount of time in the 1-day interval over which the performance monitoring information is actually counted. This value will be the same as the interval duration except in a situation where performance monitoring data could not be collected for any reason.

shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalES.name: shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalES
shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalES.description: Count of Errored Seconds (ES) during the 1-day interval as measured by hdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalMoniSecs.

shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalSES.name: shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalSES
shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalSES.description: Count of Severely Errored Seconds (SES) during the 1-day interval as measured by hdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalMoniSecs.

shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalCRCanomalies.name: shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalCRCanomalies
shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalCRCanomalies.description: Count of CRC anomalies during the 1-day interval as measured by hdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalMoniSecs.

shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalLOSWS.name: shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalLOSWS
shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalLOSWS.description: Count of Loss of Sync Word (LOSW) Seconds during the 1-day interval as measured by hdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalMoniSecs.

shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalUAS.name: shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalUAS
shehdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalUAS.description: Count of Unavailable Seconds (UAS) during the 1-day interval as measured by hdsl2Shdsl1DayIntervalMoniSecs.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintTable.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintTable
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintTable.description: This table supports maintenance operations (eg. loopbacks) to be performed on HDSL2/SHDSL segment endpoints. This table contains live data from equipment. As such, it is NOT persistent.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintEntry.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintEntry
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintEntry.description: An entry in the hdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintTable. Each entry corresponds to a single segment endpoint, and is indexed by the ifIndex of the HDSL2/SHDSL line, the UnitId of the associated unit and the side of the unit.

shehdsl2ShdslMaintLoopbackConfig.name: shehdsl2ShdslMaintLoopbackConfig
shehdsl2ShdslMaintLoopbackConfig.description: This object controls configuration of loopbacks for the associated segment endpoint. The status of the loopback is obtained via the hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrStatus object. noLoopback(1), normalLoopback(2) is available for STU-C and STU-R. specialLoopback(3), normalLoopbackEocId9(8), specialLoopbackEocId9(9) are only available for STU-R. digitalLoopback(4) analogLoopback(5) interfaceLoopBack(6) localFramerLoopback(7) are only available for STU-C. Loopmode 2 and 3 are standard defined. All other modes are proprietary and not supported by all lines.

shehdsl2ShdslMaintTipRingReversal.name: shehdsl2ShdslMaintTipRingReversal
shehdsl2ShdslMaintTipRingReversal.description: This object indicates the state of the tip/ring pair at the associated segment endpoint. normal(1), reversed(2)

shehdsl2ShdslMaintPowerBackOff.name: shehdsl2ShdslMaintPowerBackOff
shehdsl2ShdslMaintPowerBackOff.description: This object configures the receiver at the associated segment endpoint to operate in default or enhanced power backoff mode. default(1), enhanced(2) is actual not supported for STU-C disable(3) is actual not supported for STU-R

shehdsl2ShdslMaintSoftRestart.name: shehdsl2ShdslMaintSoftRestart
shehdsl2ShdslMaintSoftRestart.description: This object enables the manager to trigger a soft restart of the modem at the associated segment endpoint. The manager may only set this object to the 'restart(2)' value, which initiates a restart. The agent will perform a restart after approximately 5 seconds. Following the 5 second period, the agent will restore the object to the 'ready(1)' state.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintControlIndex.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintControlIndex
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintControlIndex.description: First key for the modified entry. IfIndex of line.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintControlStatus.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintControlStatus
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintControlTimer.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintControlTimer
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintControlReqResu.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintControlReqResult
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintControlReqResu.description: The result of the last user command.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintControlTimeSta.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintControlTimeStamp
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintControlTimeSta.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintControlSide.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintControlSide
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointMaintControlSide.description: Third key for the modified entry.

shehdsl2ShdslUnitMaintTable.name: shehdsl2ShdslUnitMaintTable
shehdsl2ShdslUnitMaintTable.description: This table supports maintenance operations for units in a HDSL2/SHDSL line. Entries in this table MUST be maintained in a persistent manner.

shehdsl2ShdslUnitMaintEntry.name: shehdsl2ShdslUnitMaintEntry
shehdsl2ShdslUnitMaintEntry.description: An entry in the hdsl2ShdslUnitMaintTable. Each entry corresponds to a single unit, and is indexed by the ifIndex of the HDSL2/SHDSL line and the UnitId of the associated unit.

shehdsl2ShdslMaintLoopbackTimeout.name: shehdsl2ShdslMaintLoopbackTimeout
shehdsl2ShdslMaintLoopbackTimeout.description: This object configures the timeout value for loopbacks initiated at segments endpoints contained in the associated unit. A value of 0 disables the timeout.

shehdsl2ShdslMaintUnitPowerSource.name: shehdsl2ShdslMaintUnitPowerSource
shehdsl2ShdslMaintUnitPowerSource.description: This object indicates the DC power source being used by the associated unit. local(1), span(2)

shehdsl2ShdslUnitMaintControlIndex.name: shehdsl2ShdslUnitMaintControlIndex
shehdsl2ShdslUnitMaintControlIndex.description: First key for the modified entry. IfIndex of line.

shehdsl2ShdslUnitMaintControlStatus.name: shehdsl2ShdslUnitMaintControlStatus
shehdsl2ShdslUnitMaintControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

shehdsl2ShdslUnitMaintControlTimer.name: shehdsl2ShdslUnitMaintControlTimer
shehdsl2ShdslUnitMaintControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

shehdsl2ShdslUnitMaintControlReqResult.name: shehdsl2ShdslUnitMaintControlReqResult
shehdsl2ShdslUnitMaintControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

shehdsl2ShdslUnitMaintControlTimeStamp.name: shehdsl2ShdslUnitMaintControlTimeStamp
shehdsl2ShdslUnitMaintControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileTable.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileTable
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileTable.description: This table supports definitions of span configuration profiles for SHDSL lines. HDSL2 does not support these configuration options. This table MUST be maintained in a persistent manner.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileEntry.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileEntry
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to a single span configuration profile. Each profile contains a set of span configuration parameters. The configuration parameters in a profile are applied to those lines referencing that profile (see the hdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfile object). If an active entry is referenced in hdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfile, the entry MUST remain active until all references are removed.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileIndex.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileIndex
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileIndex.description: A free running index for this table.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileName.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileName
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileName.description: This object is the unique index associated with this profile. Entries in this table are referenced via the object hdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfile in Hdsl2ShdslSpanConfEntry. This characters are not allowed: space : ?

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfWireInterface.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfWireInterface
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfWireInterface.description: This object configures the wire-interface operation for SHDSL Lines. twoWire(1), fourWire(2), fourWireBitInterleaved(3), fourWireByteInterleaveEnhanced(4), fourWireBitInterleaveEnhanced(5), sixWire(6), eightWire(7) Interfaces of type sdsl (96) support modes 1..5 and mode 3..5 are proprietary! Interfaces of type shdsl (169) will support mode 1..2 and 6..7!

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfMinLineRate.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfMinLineRate
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfMinLineRate.description: This object configures the minimum transmission rate for the associated SHDSL Line in bits-per-second (bps). If the minimum line rate equals the maximum line rate (hdsl2ShdslSpanMaxLineRate), the line rate is considered 'fixed'. If the minimum line rate is less than the maximum line rate, the line rate is considered 'rate-adaptive'. The minimum linerate should never be higher then the maximum linerate. Note: Technical usefull minium and maximum values depend on the configured WireInterface mode: twoWire mode -> minimum should be 200 kBits -> maximum should be 5704 kBits fourWire mode -> minimum should be 400 kBits -> maximum should be 11408 kBits sixWire mode -> minimum should be 600 kBits -> maximum should be 17112 kBits eigthWire mode -> minimum should be 800 kBits -> maximum should be 22816 kBits

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfMaxLineRate.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfMaxLineRate
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfMaxLineRate.description: This object configures the maximum transmission rate for the associated SHDSL Line in bits-per-second (bps). If the minimum line rate equals the maximum line rate (hdsl2ShdslSpanMaxLineRate), the line rate is considered 'fixed'. If the minimum line rate is less than the maximum line rate, the line rate is considered 'rate-adaptive'. The maximum linerate should never be less then the minimum linerate. Note: Technical usefull minium and maximum values depend on the configured WireInterface mode: twoWire mode -> minimum should be 200 kBits -> maximum should be 5704 kBits fourWire mode -> minimum should be 400 kBits -> maximum should be 11408 kBits sixWire mode -> minimum should be 600 kBits -> maximum should be 17112 kBits eigthWire mode -> minimum should be 800 kBits -> maximum should be 22816 kBits

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfPSD.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfPSD
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfPSD.description: This object configures use of symmetric/asymmetric PSD (Power Spectral Density) Mask for the associated SHDSL Line. Support for symmetric PSD is mandatory for all supported data rates. Support for asymmetric PSD is optional. symmetric(1), asymmetric(2), r1Asymmetric(3), r2Asymmetric(4) Mode 3..4 are propietary and only supported by interfaces of type sdsl (96).

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfTransmissionMode.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfTransmissionMode
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfTransmissionMode.description: This object specifies the regional setting for the SHDSL line. Minimum of one bit should always be set! Bit Meaning Description 1 region 1 Indicates ITU-T G.991.2 Annex A/F. 2 region 2 Indicates ITU-T G.991.2 Annex B/G.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfRemoteEnabled.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfRemoteEnabled
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfRemoteEnabled.description: This object enables/disables support for remote management of the units in a SHDSL line from the STU-R via the EOC. enabled(1), disabled(2)

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfPowerFeeding.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfPowerFeeding
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfPowerFeeding.description: This object enables/disables support for optional power feeding in a SHDSL line. noPower(1), powerFeed(2), wettingCurrent(3)

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfCurrCondTargetMargi.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfCurrCondTargetMarginDown
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfCurrCondTargetMargi.description: This object specifies the downstream current condition target SNR margin for a SHDSL line. The SNR margin is the difference between the desired SNR and the actual SNR. Target SNR margin is the desired SNR margin for a unit.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfWorstCaseTargetMarg.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfWorstCaseTargetMarginDown
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfWorstCaseTargetMarg.description: This object specifies the downstream worst case target SNR margin for a SHDSL line. The SNR margin is the difference between the desired SNR and the actual SNR. Target SNR margin is the desired SNR margin for a unit.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfCurrCondTargetMargi.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfCurrCondTargetMarginUp
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfCurrCondTargetMargi.description: This object specifies the upstream current condition target SNR margin for a SHDSL line. The SNR margin is the difference between the desired SNR and the actual SNR. Target SNR margin is the desired SNR margin for a unit.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfWorstCaseTargetMarg.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfWorstCaseTargetMarginUp
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfWorstCaseTargetMarg.description: This object specifies the upstream worst case target SNR margin for a SHDSL line. The SNR margin is the difference between the desired SNR and the actual SNR. Target SNR margin is the desired SNR margin for a unit.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfUsedTargetMargins.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfUsedTargetMargins
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfUsedTargetMargins.description: Contains indicates whether a target SNR margin is enabled or disabled. This is a bit-map of possible settings. Minimum of one bit should always be set! The various bit positions are: currCondDown current condition downstream target SNR margin enabled worstCaseDown worst case downstream target SNR margin enabled currCondUp current condition upstream target SNR margin enabled worstCaseUp worst case upstream target SNR margin enabled.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfReferenceClock.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfReferenceClock
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfReferenceClock.description: This object configures the clock reference for the STU-C in a SHDSL Line. Note: Interfaces of type sdsl (96) support only value localClk(1). Interfaces of type shdsl (169) support also the mode networkClk(2).

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfLineProbeEnable.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfLineProbeEnable
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfLineProbeEnable.description: This object enables/disables support for Line Probe of the units in a SHDSL line. When Line Probe is enabled, the system performs Line Probing to find the best possible rate. If Line probe is disabled, the rate adaptation phase is skipped to shorten set up time. disable(1), enable(2)

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfPAMConstellation.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfPAMConstellation
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfPAMConstellation.description: The parameter allows the selection of which PAM constellation is to be used. - AUTO_PAM_SELECT - Automatic PAM selection - SELECT_16_PAM - Use 16 PAM only - SELECT_32_PAM - Use 32 PAM only Select 16Pam limits the data rates from 192 kbps to 3840 kbps Select 32Pam limits the data rates from 768 kbps to 5696 kbps +a--------------------------------------------------------+ | Soc4e-Dsl-API : SHDSL_LineTcPamSelModeGet | +---------------------------------------------------------+ | SHDSL_TcPamSelMode_t * pMode | | pointer to store current TC-PAM selection mode | ++--------------------------------------------------------+ | extented | +---------------------------------------------------------+ This is propietary extension for interfaces of type shdsl (169) only.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfTCLayerSupported.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfTCLayerSupported
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfTCLayerSupported.description: Specifies the TC-Layer. Set fix to 80)/ DSL_TC_ATM. (0) - DSL_TC_ATM (1) - DSL_TC_EFM (2) - DSL_TC_HDLC +a--------------------------------------------------------+ | Soc4e-Dsl-API : DSL_SystemInterfaceConfigGet | +---------------------------------------------------------+ | DSL_SystemInterfaceConfig_t * pData | | DSL_TcLayerSelection_t | +d--------------------------------------------------------+ | Soc4e-Drv-Cmd : ACK_PMD_EndpointAlarmConfig | +x--------------------------------------------------------+ | sics <line> <nTcLayer> <nSystemIf> | +---------------------------------------------------------+ This is propietary extension for interfaces of type shdsl (169) only.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlIndex.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlIndex
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlIndex.description: Key for the modified or deleted entry. NE will choose this number during create.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlStatu.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlStatus
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlStatu.description: The status of a user command.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlTimer.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlTimer
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlReqRe.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlReqResult
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlReqRe.description: The result of the last user command.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlTimeS.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlTimeStamp
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlTimeS.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlWireI.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlWireInterface
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlWireI.description: Look at table. twoWire(1), fourWire(2), fourWireBitInterleaved(3), fourWireByteInterleaveEnhanced(4), fourWireBitInterleaveEnhanced(5), sixWire(6), eightWire(7) Interfaces of type sdsl (96) support modes 1..5 and mode 3..5 are proprietary! Interfaces of type shdsl (169) will support mode 1..2 and 6..7!

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlMinLi.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlMinLineRate
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlMinLi.description: Look at table. Note: Technical usefull minium and maximum values depend on the configured WireInterface mode: twoWire mode -> minimum should be 200 kBits -> maximum should be 5704 kBits fourWire mode -> minimum should be 400 kBits -> maximum should be 11408 kBits sixWire mode -> minimum should be 600 kBits -> maximum should be 17112 kBits eigthWire mode -> minimum should be 800 kBits -> maximum should be 22816 kBits

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlMaxLi.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlMaxLineRate
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlMaxLi.description: Look at table. Note: Technical usefull minium and maximum values depend on the configured WireInterface mode: twoWire mode -> minimum should be 200 kBits -> maximum should be 5704 kBits fourWire mode -> minimum should be 400 kBits -> maximum should be 11408 kBits sixWire mode -> minimum should be 600 kBits -> maximum should be 17112 kBits eigthWire mode -> minimum should be 800 kBits -> maximum should be 22816 kBits

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlRefer.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlReferenceClock
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlRefer.description: Look at table. Note: Interfaces of type sdsl (96) support only value localClk(1). Interfaces of type shdsl (169) support also the mode networkClk(2).

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlPAMCo.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlPAMConstellation
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlPAMCo.description: Look at table. This is propietary extension for interfaces of type shdsl (169) only.

shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlTCLay.name: shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlTCLayerSupported
shehdsl2ShdslSpanConfProfileControlTCLay.description: Look at table. This is propietary extension for interfaces of type shdsl (169) only.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileTab.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileTable
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileTab.description: This table supports definitions of alarm configuration profiles for HDSL2/SHDSL segment endpoints. This table MUST be maintained in a persistent manner.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileEnt.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileEntry
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileEnt.description: Each entry corresponds to a single alarm configuration profile. Each profile contains a set of parameters for setting alarm thresholds for various performance attributes monitored at HDSL2/SHDSL segment endpoints. Profiles may be created/deleted using the row creation/deletion mechanism via hdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileRowStatus. If an active entry is referenced in either hdsl2ShdslSpanConfAlarmProfile or hdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfile, the entry MUST remain active until all references are removed.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileInd.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileIndex
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileInd.description: A free running index for this table.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileNam.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileName
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileNam.description: This object is the unique index associated with this profile. This characters are not allowed: space : ?

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshLoopAttenuati.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshLoopAttenuation
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshLoopAttenuati.description: This object configures the loop attenuation alarm threshold. When the current value of hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrAtn reaches or exceeds this threshold, a hdsl2ShdslLoopAttenCrossing MAY be generated.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshSNRMargin.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshSNRMargin
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshSNRMargin.description: This object configures the SNR margin alarm threshold. When the current value of hdsl2ShdslEndpointCurrSnrMgn reaches or drops below this threshold, a hdsl2ShdslSNRMarginCrossing MAY be generated.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshES.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshES
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshES.description: This object configures the threshold for the number of errored seconds (ES) within any given 15-minute performance data collection interval. If the value of errored seconds in a particular 15-minute collection interval reaches/ exceeds this value, a hdsl2ShdslPerfESThresh MAY be generated. At most one notification will be sent per interval per endpoint.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshSES.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshSES
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshSES.description: This object configures the threshold for the number of severely errored seconds (SES) within any given 15-minute performance data collection interval. If the value of severely errored seconds in a particular 15-minute collection interval reaches/exceeds this value, a hdsl2ShdslPerfSESThresh MAY be generated. At most one notification will be sent per interval per endpoint.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshCRCanomalies.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshCRCanomalies
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshCRCanomalies.description: This object configures the threshold for the number of CRC anomalies within any given 15-minute performance data collection interval. If the value of CRC anomalies in a particular 15-minute collection interval reaches/exceeds this value, a hdsl2ShdslPerfCRCanomaliesThresh MAY be generated. At most one notification will be sent per interval per endpoint.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshLOSWS.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshLOSWS
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshLOSWS.description: This object configures the threshold for the number of Loss of Sync Word (LOSW) Seconds within any given 15-minute performance data collection interval. If the value of LOSW in a particular 15-minute collection interval reaches/exceeds this value, a hdsl2ShdslPerfLOSWSThresh MAY be generated. At most one notification will be sent per interval per endpoint.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshUAS.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshUAS
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshUAS.description: This object configures the threshold for the number of unavailable seconds (UAS) within any given 15-minute performance data collection interval. If the value of UAS in a particular 15-minute collection interval reaches/exceeds this value, a hdsl2ShdslPerfUASThresh MAY be generated. At most one notification will be sent per interval per endpoint.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileCon.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileControlIndex
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileCon.description: Key for the modified or deleted entry. NE will choose this number during create.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileCon.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileControlStatus
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileCon.description: The status of a user command.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileCon.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileControlTimer
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileCon.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileCon.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileControlReqResult
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileCon.description: The result of the last user command.

shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileCon.name: shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileControlTimeStamp
shehdsl2ShdslEndpointAlarmConfProfileCon.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

shehdsl2ShdslLoopAttenCrossing.name: shehdsl2ShdslLoopAttenCrossing
shehdsl2ShdslLoopAttenCrossing.description: This notification indicates that the loop attenuation threshold (as per the hdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshLoopAttenuation value) has been reached/exceeded for the HDSL2/SHDSL segment endpoint.

shehdsl2ShdslSNRMarginCrossing.name: shehdsl2ShdslSNRMarginCrossing
shehdsl2ShdslSNRMarginCrossing.description: This notification indicates that the SNR margin threshold (as per the hdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshSNRMargin value) has been reached/exceeded for the HDSL2/SHDSL segment endpoint.

shehdsl2ShdslPerfESThresh.name: shehdsl2ShdslPerfESThresh
shehdsl2ShdslPerfESThresh.description: This notification indicates that the errored seconds threshold (as per the hdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshES value) has been reached/ exceeded for the HDSL2/SHDSL segment endpoint.

shehdsl2ShdslPerfSESThresh.name: shehdsl2ShdslPerfSESThresh
shehdsl2ShdslPerfSESThresh.description: This notification indicates that the severely errored seconds threshold (as per the hdsl2ShdslEndpointThreshSES value) has been reached/exceeded for the HDSL2/SHDSL Segment Endpoint.
